review_blob: Generally like central waters but couldnt make it thru more than 1/3 of a bottle on 2 occasions. Soapy taste with a strong finish. The hops pop at the end but just dont care for this variety.
beer_name: Central Waters Hop Rise Session Ale

review_blob: 12 pk from woodmans in Appleton. Great Winter beer, now a keeper. Heavy on the malt, coffee and cocoa. Right amount of alcohol to balance it all out!
beer_name: Central Waters Satin Solitude Imperial Stout

review_blob: Batch 6 bottle.  Binnys in Lake Zurich, IL.  Strong flavors of licorice, chocolate notes and fruit.  The twist of double espresso on the bad end is very interesting.  I would equate it to drinking campfire ashes, worth a try if you can get it.

Glad to have Stone in Illinois finally.  Spring 2010 Limited release.  This beer is everything it says it is.  Great balance, wonderful aroma that is not overpowering, Perfect mouth feel wonderful transition of all the flavors that lurk inside!
All one could home for in an oatmeal stout!  Outstanding flavors of coffee, excellent balance of everything else.  Aroma is tame but enjoyable, great beer!

Reminds me of the pilsners that can only be gotten on tap in Germany.  Color, head, aroma are as good as it gets for a pils.  Flavor is amazing.  This is as good a bottled pilsner that can be found stateside.

Wee heavy is right.  A glass of this at the bar leads to springy knees when getting off the stool.  Very tasty, served in a very large schooner glass.  Dark depp color and excellent flavor all the way down.
beer_name: Mickey Finns Wee Heavy Scottish Ale

review_blob: Nice malt flavor and well balanced with the hops.  Aroma is amazing, but the flavor doesnt match it.

This was a pleasant suprise!  I actually bought the beer for chili because it was cheap, and the chocolate flavors would add some interesting highlights.  It comes in a 4 pack and I only needed a bottle so I decided to give it a try.  I had very low expectations, because it is a miller product, but would rate this in the top 25% of the dark beers I have tried.  It is a ways off from some of the top of the line porters, but the cost and availability offset that.  Drinking it is an interesting experience; When raising the glass one is hit by the aroma of coffee.  At first sip you will taste mild hints of cocoa.  Right before you swallow, it turns into a roasted vanilla flavor.  I would get it again, and it is a palateable option.  But I am not going to go out of my way to find it.

I really enjoyed this one.  The flavor is not typical of the english styles, its just not all that bitter.  the hops are fruity and the beer is refreshing.  there is a pinch of quickly disapating bitterness in the begining. very good but not one that most people who like english styles would enjoy. its an english for us germans.
beer_name: Black Sheep Monty Pythons Holy Grail (Bottle)

review_blob: limited amount of head and what is there disapates quickly.  the color is unmistakeable.  not the most complex hefe out there, but its very earthy and refreshing.  the malt and wheat shine thru and the citrus hits you on the back end.

Aroma reminds me of halls or robitussin, cherry flavor of course.  very crisp and refreshing with a certain sweetness to it. it has a hint of tart on the back end. its questionable to call this stuff a beer, but its pretty good.

beer_brewer_name: Schneider Weisse G. Schneider & Sohn GmbH
review_blob: Crisp and refreshing. its a little lighter than your average hefe.  the head dissapates quick and more flavors come out as it warms.  schneider makes good stuff.

An exceptional brew.  those ahops are form the pacific northwest i believe.  very floral with a hint of bitterness.  interesting color and lace that sticks.  this one is worth trying if you find it.  btw it will get ya pretty hammered.
UPDATED: FEB 23, 2004
I probably should just cut and paste my response for all the japanese beers.  clear light and fizzy.  not much going on there are a lot better out there. but with japanese food its great.
The japanese brews are not bad, they go great with the food. the flavor is not strong. this one has a little more going on on the back end than some of its counterparts.
Smooth and dry finish. no much taste or alcohol here but you must appreciate its purpose, its great with japanese food.

Interesting.  from the time it pours to the time you swallow its quite different.  when it pours there is no head, then the head seems to rise from the depths and pulls togther to make a marvelous creation.  it looks thick but interestingly its not when you drink it.  the right work for the mouthfeel is silky.  there is a mild amount of malt sweetness and cherry that makes this one a keeper.

Taste like dried apricots more than fresh ones. most would call it a little on the sour side, i would call it more tart than sour.  not bad but i am sure there are much better lambic out there.  it was a little dry on the finish, i would have like there to be a hint of spice, but thats just me.

beer_brewer_name: Schneider Weisse G. Schneider & Sohn GmbH
review_blob: Wow lots of alcohol in this one.  the thing that really turned me off was the massive amount of floaties in this bottle.  definately a dessert beer, one 12 oz bottle is more than enough.

beer_brewer_name: Schneider Weisse G. Schneider & Sohn GmbH
review_blob: Consistent quality throughout.  a hint of carmel on swallowing.  storng flavor of alcohol but it blends in nicely with the rest of the flavors.  this one is a winner.

One thing i noticed about it was the buttery taste after it went down.  the color of it was surisingly light.  Massive head on there too. pretty common around here so i might have to pick it up again.

Lot better than i originally expected.  Its somewhat like Guiness, only a lot better.  It doesnt have the bitterness or finish that guiness has.  the roasted malt give this stuff a great chocoalaty flavor.  even thought it is a dark beer, this is something you can drink a few of....
Outstanding lager with a hint of spice to it.  Doesn't finish dry at all and goes down very smooth.  had mine in a .5 L bottle.  light hoppiness and very good beer with sausage and saurkraut.

Lighest beer i have tried in the weihenstephaner line.  this is quick an upgrade from american piss.  The problem is that this brewer has a lot better to offer, so when it comes down to it, there is better in the same place for the same money.

this was the first of the 6 that were on my paddle.  its very drinkable.  once again the hops are uniue to this place and give off a nice floral flavor.  although in this brew its rather mild compared to the others.

I believe this was wahat they called scotch ale when i was there. it has a bitter taste on the front end and a sweet taste one the back end.  the color is a deep red.  definately worth a sample if your inthe area.
Once again the floral hops are the key here.  Its indicative of all thier brews.  the hops is a large component of each of thier brews.
can't really say to much about this one since i am not a fan of oatmeal stout.  i will say that it was true to the style and its part of the sampler paddle emmetts has.
Veyr much like your standard american fare, with two exceptions.  it has the special floral hops to give it the flavor and smell.  the other exception is the creaminess.  this is good stuff.

Its all in the hops!  storng floral notes, a very interesting IPA.  they get thier hops from the pacific northwest and thats true to all thier styles.  they all have a floral bouquet.  all the beers are very drinkable.  i would classify them as your typical english, scoth and irish styles with the special floral hops.
Great color.  nice head.  reminds me of a dry wine.  the finish is somewhat dry and a very good beer once in a while.
take a traditional marzen, a handful of fireplace ashes and shake well.  thats what this beer is.  this is the first beer i have dumped in a long time. just plain aweful!
Probably should have saved the money and got a miller lite instead.  either way it was not a pleasant experience.  you can drink this stuff but there is a lot better out there.

Pretty disappointed with this one.  maybe i got a bad one but it was very sour almost like vinegar was added to it.  its smells as if there is a lot of alcohol in it, but there isn't much to it this one, alcohol or flavor.  Lot of yeast settled in the bottom of bottle.  there are many hefe's out there thats are a lot better and i will be drinking those from now on.
A drier Pils.  good clean crisp taste.  something that one could enjoy with a meal or drink a lot of.  would not be a bad everyday beer.
Wheaty.  smells of wheat, taste of wheat looks of wheat.  this is a good beer if you like wheat.  which i do.
Very hoppy, very dry.  Its almost like a IPA thats dry and has no finish.  Not bad but not something to go out of your way for.
Not as dark as i thought it would be.  Not as thick as i thoughtit would be. Yet like any of paulaner's other brews, this stuff its pretty good.
Starts lightly and finishes strong.  a lot of the flavor is on the back end. ginger, chocolate, and roasted malt are the primary elements.  definately a good one to enjoy on a cold night by the fire.

Definately a good beer, its a local brew in the lake county region so it can be pretty hard to find.  They put a lime in mine the first time, and if you need to add fruit to a beer you need a different beer, this one is the exception to the rule, if you get a chance sample this one.
This stuff kind of sucks. It wasn't to bad when i started drinking it but as it warmed up a little it was like drinking cat urine.
Huge Head! A weiss eeer glass is s must with this stuff. a an excellent brew but still a hair below the weihenstephaner.
UPDATED: FEB 13, 2004
Very similar to becks but doesn't turn the corner like becks does.  Nice hoppy flavor and finishes with a pinch of bitterness. quite enjoyable.
In the same class, as heine, and pilsner urquell.  maybe even becks.  quite skunky upon opening, and not something i really enjoy, but in a pinch it does fine.
I always enjoy drinking a little of this once in a while.  just has a good quality flavor and finishes nicely.  consistent flavor from bottle to bottle.
Definately taste the alcohol. would be very good with an italian meal, tomato sauces and stuff. almost like a wine.

can;t say that i have ever tried drinking urine, but if i were to drink it i would imagine it would taste quite a bit like his brew.  the warmer this stuff gets, the more it taste like a scoop out of a urinal.
